Assign Azure Policy:

-Search for "Azure Policy" in the portal and navigate to it.
-Search for "Allowed Locations" policy.
-Click "Assign Policy" and enter the details:
-Scope, Resource Group, Policy Definition, Allowed Locations, Name, Description.
-In Parameters, select "Central India."
-Click "Create" to assign the policy.

Testing the Policy:

-Created a Virtual Network in "Central India" — Success.
-Created a Storage Account in "East US" — Failure.
